value.value: Mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase 5 (1374 aa, ~155 kDa) is encoded by the human MAP3K5 gene. This protein is involved in the apoptosis signal transduction pathway through mitochondria-dependent caspase activation.

label.value: Dual Specificity Mitogen-Activated Protein Kinase Kinase 2

value.value: Dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 2 (400 aa, ~44 kDa) is encoded by the human MAP2K2 gene. This protein plays a role in protein phosphorylation.

This gene may be involved in the modulation of protein SET activity.

Human SETBP1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 18q21.1 and is approximately 388 kb in length. This allele, which encodes SET-binding protein, may play a role in the regulation of protein SET activity. Mutation of the gene is associated with Schinzel-Giedion midface retraction syndrome. A chromosomal translocation, t(11;18)(p15;q12), involving this gene and the NUP98 gene is involved in T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia.
SET-binding protein (1596 aa, ~175 kDa) is encoded by the human SETBP1 gene. This protein is involved in binding to protein SET.
This gene plays a role in the biosynthesis of cyclic dinucleotides.

Human CGAS wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6q13 and is approximately 39 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cyclic GMP-AMP synthase protein, is involved in both immunity and cyclic nucleotide synthesis.
Cyclic GMP-AMP synthase (522 aa, ~59 kDa) is encoded by the human CGAS gene. This protein plays a role both cyclic dinucleotide synthesis and immune response activation.
This gene is involved in both apolipoprotein A-I binding and nicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide metabolism.

Human NAXE wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q22 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes NAD(P)H-hydrate epimerase protein, is involved in both NAD metabolism and apolipoprotein A-I binding.
The process of manufacturing prescription medications for humans by a pharmaceutical company.
NAD(P)H-hydrate epimerase (288 aa, ~32 kDa) is encoded by the human NAXE gene. This protein is involved in both lipoprotein binding and nucleotide metabolism.
The process of manufacturing non-prescription medications for humans by a pharmaceutical company.

A question about whether an individual has or had a moderate likelihood of dozing.
A question about whether an individual has or had a high likelihood of dozing.
